    "Backstory": "The Ghost E46 is often called the last true driver's M car. Before turbocharging, before excessive weight, before screens everywhere - it was just a perfectly balanced chassis with an engine that begged to be revved. The S54 inline-six with individual throttle bodies is a mechanical masterpiece, pulling to 8000 RPM with a sound that makes grown enthusiasts weep. The 50/50 weight distribution means it does exactly what you ask, when you ask it. It's not the fastest car, but it might be the most rewarding to drive at the limit.",
